    {
      "id": 347501,
      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "The benzylammonium ion (C<sub>6</sub>H<sub>5</sub>CH<sub>2</sub>NH<sub>3</sub><sup>+</sup>) has p<i>K</i><sub>a</sub> = 9.33, and the propylammonium ion has p<i>K</i><sub>a</sub> = 10.71. Which is the stronger base, benzylamine or propylamine? What are the p<i>K</i><sub>b</sub>’s of benzylamine and propylamine?",
      "answers": [],
      "hints": [],
      "formats": [
        "free-response"
      ],
      "combo_choices": [],
      "collaborator_solutions": [
        {
          "images": [],
          "solution_type": "detailed",
          "content_html": "Propylamine is stronger; benzylamine p<i>K</i><sub>b</sub> = 4.67; propylamine p<i>K</i><sub>b</sub> = 3.29"
        }
      ],
